Rohit Shetty, who brings together Shah Rukh Khan and Kajol on screen after a five-year gap in Dilwale , insists his film is not a remake of Chalti Ka Naam Gaadi . Bollywood lovers will have the opportunity to crush over Shah Rukh Khan and Kajol, arguably the most romantic pair of Hindi cinema, all over again. Shetty rubbishes rumours about his film being a remake, stating that he had the script from the time he was making Chennai Express (2013). He says, &#8220;There were many speculations about the cast, but it is Shah Rukh and Kajol. Varun Dhawan and Kriti Sanon are also part of the film. And it&#8217;s not a remake. It&#8217;s an action-comedy, suited for family audiences.